{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}{\colortbl;\red31\green41\blue55;\red14\green94\blue168;\red92\green107\blue119;}\paperw12240\paperh15840\margl720\margr720\margt720\margb720\pard\qc\sa80\f0\fs32 \b Active Adult Performance and Greystar Counter Brief\b0\par
\pard\qc\sa180\f0\fs18 Prepared March 13, 2026 using the internal snapshot export dated 2026-03-13T01:18:47.321Z.\par
\pard\ql\sa180\f0\fs22 Bottom line: the updated snapshot shows three communities in different lease-up stages, not a clean case that the current operator lacks 55+ capability. One of the three assets is still in phased delivery, and Greystar does not appear to have meaningful active-adult operating depth in Jacksonville or Ponte Vedra.\par
\pard\ql\sa120\f0\fs26 \b Executive Takeaways\b0\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - Updated Viera data shows 53.0% occupied and 57.2% leased, only 7 occupied units and 5 leased units off March targets.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - Nocatee and Glen Kernan Park should not be judged against stabilized 55+ comps. Nocatee remains an early lease-up and Glen Kernan Park remains a phased-delivery asset.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - NIC reported 91.9% active-adult occupancy in 4Q25 across the sector, while stabilized active-adult communities open at least two years averaged about 95% occupied.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - Industry sources note that upscale active-adult communities often lease more slowly because many prospects need to sell a home first, so raw traffic volume is a weak standalone scorecard.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - I could not verify any Greystar-managed active-adult rental community in Jacksonville or Ponte Vedra. The only current Greystar-managed public comp I confirmed in the broader scope is Parasol Melbourne.\par
