\pard\ql\sa100\f0\fs26 \b Property Detail\b0\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs24 \b Viera\b0\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Updated March snapshot shows Viera slightly behind March budget but still within a manageable unit gap for a new active-adult lease-up.\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Mar snapshot: 88 occupied (53.0%) and 95 leased (57.2%) on 166 units.\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Gap to current budget: 7 occupied units and 5 leased units to target.\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Current funnel: 23 guest cards, 9 tours, 4 applications, and 0 signed leases.\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Conversion view: lead-to-tour 39.1%, tour-to-app 44.4%, lead-to-lease 0.0%, app-to-lease 0.0%.\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Absorption: +0 in Mar; Q1 net absorption +1.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs24 \b Nocatee\b0\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Nocatee is further off its current budget curve, but it remains in early active-adult lease-up rather than a mature stabilized position.\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Mar snapshot: 104 occupied (58.4%) and 115 leased (64.6%) on 178 units.\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Gap to current budget: 16 occupied units and 10 leased units to target.\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Current funnel: 21 guest cards, 9 tours, 1 applications, and 1 signed leases.\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Conversion view: lead-to-tour 42.9%, tour-to-app 11.1%, lead-to-lease 4.8%, app-to-lease 100.0%.\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Absorption: +1 in Mar; Q1 net absorption -1.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs24 \b Glen Kernan Park\b0\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Glen Kernan Park is still a phased-delivery community, so its performance should be framed as an in-delivery lease-up, not a stabilized comp.\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Mar snapshot: 30 occupied (9.7%) and 43 leased (14.0%) on 308 units.\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Gap to current budget: 16 occupied units and 16 leased units to target.\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Current funnel: 27 guest cards, 11 tours, 3 applications, and 6 signed leases.\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Conversion view: lead-to-tour 40.7%, tour-to-app 27.3%, lead-to-lease 22.2%, app-to-lease 200.0%.\par
\pard\ql\sa55\f0\fs22 - Absorption: +5 in Mar; Q1 net absorption +12.\par
\pard\ql\sa100\f0\fs26 \b Why the Benchmark Needs to Be Corrected\b0\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - RISE Viera and RISE at Nocatee were 2024 deliveries and held their grand openings in January 2025.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - RISE at Glen Kernan Park was announced as a phased community with first units delivering in summer 2025 and the balance in summer 2026.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - NIC's 4Q25 active-adult occupancy reading was 91.9% across the category, not the 95% stabilized benchmark ownership may be using.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - NIC separately notes stabilized active-adult communities open at least two years have averaged about 95% occupancy.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - NIC's industry discussion featuring Carlyle and Overture notes higher-end active-adult communities often lease more slowly because prospects may first need to sell a single-family home.\par
\pard\ql\sa100\f0\fs26 \b Greystar Counterpoints\b0\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - Greystar's official active-adult platform highlights brands such as Overture, Everleigh, and Album, but I did not verify a Greystar-managed active-adult rental community in Jacksonville or Ponte Vedra.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - Parasol Melbourne is the only clear Greystar-managed comp I found in the broader Viera/Melbourne scope.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - Public listings for Parasol Melbourne currently show availability and concessions, including 14 to 15 available units and up to six weeks free, which suggests a low-90s occupied or committed position rather than a clearly stronger local outcome.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - RISE publicly markets a dedicated 55+ active-living platform and already operates communities in the exact Florida geographies under discussion.\par
\pard\ql\sa100\f0\fs26 \b Recommended Talking Points\b0\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - We should evaluate these assets against active-adult lease-up benchmarks, not fully stabilized two-year-plus communities.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - Viera's current March gap is measurable and manageable: 7 occupied units and 5 leased units to plan.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - Glen Kernan Park is still in phased delivery, so comparing it to fully delivered 55+ communities misstates performance.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - Higher-end active-adult product naturally produces slower lead velocity than conventional multifamily because prospects often coordinate a home sale before moving.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - Greystar does not appear to have stronger local submarket proof in Jacksonville or Ponte Vedra, and its nearest confirmed comp in Melbourne still appears to be using concessions.\par
\pard\ql\sa70\f0\fs22 - RISE already has in-market 55+ operating experience across these locations, which is more relevant than national brand recognition alone.\par
